#Text=Antje
#Text=Duvekot on life as a folk singer , her family and her music
#Text=Sunday , November 11 , 2007

#Text=Boston-based singer-songwriter Antje Duvekot has made a name for herself in the folk music world with powerful ballads of heartbreak and longing for a deeper spirituality , but coming up empty-handed .
#Text=Below is David Shankbone 's interview with the folk chanteuse .
#Text=David Shankbone : Tell me about your new album .
#Text=Antje Duvekot : It ’s called Big Dream Boulevard and it ’s the first studio album I made .
#Text=It ’s not so new ; I made it in May of 2006 .
#Text=It ’s produced by Séamus Egan , who is the leader of a fairly renowned band named Solas .
#Text=DS : You mentioned you used to explore more dark themes in your work , but that lately you are exploring lighter fare .
#Text=What themes are you exploring on this album ?
#Text=AD : In the future I am hoping for more light themes .
#Text=I feel like I have worked through a lot of the darkness , and personally I feel like I ’m ready to write a batch of lighter songs , but that ’s just how I ’m feeling right now .
#Text=My last record , Big Dream Boulevard , was a pretty heavy record and that was not intentional .
#Text=I write what is on my mind .
#Text=DS : What were you going through that made it so dark ?
#Text=AD : The record is drawn from my whole writing career , so it ’s old and new songs as well .
#Text=I was n’t going through anything in particular because it was spanning a wide time period .
#Text=I think it ’s fair to say that over all I turn to music in times of trouble and need as a therapeutic tool to get me through sadness .
#Text=That ’s why I tend to turn to music .
#Text=So my songs tend to be a little darker , because that ’s where I tend to go for solace .
#Text=So themes like personal struggle with relationships and existential issues .
#Text=DS : What personal relationships do you struggle with ?
#Text=AD : A lot of my songs are about dating and relationship troubles .
#Text=That ’s one category .
#Text=But a lot of my songs are about existential questions because I struggle with what to believe in .
#Text=DS : Do you believe in a higher power ?
#Text=AD : I ’m sort of an atheist who wishes I could believe something .
#Text=DS : What do you believe ?
#Text=AD : It ’s undefined .
#Text=I think I ’m spiritual in music , which is my outlet , but I just ca n’t get on board with an organized religion .
#Text=Not even Unitarianism .
#Text=I do miss something like that in my life , though .
#Text=DS : Why do you miss having religion in your life ?
#Text=AD : I think every human being craves a feeling that there is a higher purpose .
#Text=It ’s a need for me .
#Text=A lot of my songs express that struggle .
